  "description": "Divisibility is the fundamental relation of multiplicative number theory: it asks whether one integer fits evenly into another. We say that aa divides bb (written a∣ba \\mid b) if there exists an integer kk such that b=akb = ak — that is, bb is a multiple of aa, and aa is a divisor (or factor) of bb. The number 3 divides 12 because 12=3×412 = 3 \\times 4. The number 5 does not divide 12 because there is no integer kk with 12=5k12 = 5k.\n",
